OL,3,CSunak to warn against 'over-
OL,4,Cmedicalising everyday worries' in
OL,5,Cwelfare speech
OL,7,FThe speech comes a month after Work
OL,8,Fand Pensions Secretary Mel Stride
OL,9,Ffaced criticism for an interview in
OL,10,Fwhich he said there was "a real risk"
OL,11,Fthat "the normal ups and downs of
OL,12,Fhuman life" were being labelled as
OL,13,Fmedical conditions which then held
OL,14,Fpeople back from working.
OL,16,FThose comments were described as
OL,17,F"disappointing" by the president of
OL,18,Fthe Royal College of Psychiatrists,
OL,19,Fwhile the Centre for Mental Health
OL,20,Fcharity said they risked "belittling
OL,21,Fpeople's struggles".
