OL,5,Cwelfare speech
OL,7,FMr Sunak is expected to refer to
OL,8,Fchallenges presented since the
OL,9,Fpandemic, with the Government saying a
OL,10,F"significant number of working aged
OL,11,Fpeople have become inactive due to
OL,12,Flong term sickness which has in large
OL,13,Fpart been driven by mental health
OL,14,Fconditions".
OL,16,FHe is expected to say: "We don't just
OL,17,Fneed to change the sick note, we need
OL,18,Fto change the sick note culture so the
OL,19,Fdefault becomes what work you can do `
OL,20,Fnot what you can't.
