OL,7,FSince 2020, the number of people out
OL,8,Fof work due to long-term sickness has
OL,9,Frisen significantly, reaching a record
OL,10,Fhigh of 2.8 million people as of
OL,11,FFebruary 2024, according to the latest
OL,12,Festimates from the Office for National
OL,13,FStatistics.
OL,15,FA large proportion of those report
OL,16,Fsuffering from depression, bad nerves
OL,17,For anxiety, although most of those
OL,18,Freport these as secondary conditions
OL,19,Frather than the main one keeping them
OL,20,Fout of work.
